Johannesburg - The Gauteng member of the executive council (MEC) for community safety, Sizakele Nkosi-Malobane, will hold routine review meetings to reflect on the annual performance and quarterly reports of provincial law enforcement agencies, the department said on Thursday. Nkosi-Malobane will on Friday meet with the leadership of the provincial law enforcement agencies including the provincial Police Commissioner, Lt Gen Deliwe de Lange and her management team in Johannesburg. Some of the issues that will also be discussed include police conduct, and the police's compliance with the domestic violence act. African News Agency (ANA)